APARTMENTINFOMODAL.title: Apartment number
APARTMENTINFOMODAL.text1: An apartment number consists of four digits and is used by the Tax Agency to identify apartments.
APARTMENTINFOMODAL.text2: The first two numbers indicate the floor. Entrance level is set to 10 and floors above are numbered 11, 12, etc. Floor plan below the entrance is set to 09, 08, etc.
APARTMENTINFOMODAL.text3: The last two numbers indicate the position of the home on the floor. The residence directly to the left of the stairs, when approaching the floor level from below, is set to 01. Numbering then continues clockwise.

helpWith: What do you want help with?
additionalSpacePopupText: Additional area refers to space in the home that don’t count towards the residence size, such as a garage, balcony or storage. Leave this field empty if you don’t have any additional area.

tax_deduction_description1: Tax deduction is a tax reduction for services close to the household, such as moving assistance and moving cleaning. If you are entitled to a tax deduction, you only pay 50% of the work cost.
tax_deduction_description2: The maximum sum for "Rot" and "Rut" deductions is SEK 75,000 per year (of which a maximum of SEK 50,000 rot  deductions).
tax_deduction_description3: You can retrieve your data from the Swedish Tax Agency, if you want to see your current balance here on Flyttsmart.
tax_deduction_description4_Text: Read more on the Swedish Tax Agency's website.
